 The Star Model PD is a compact and lightweight semi-automatic pistol which was manufactured from 1975 to 1990 by the firearms manufacturing company Star Bonifacio Echeverria, S.A., located in the city of Eibar in the Basque region of Spain.[1]

The Model PD can be loaded with six .45 ACP pistol cartridges in the detachable internal magazine, plus one in the chamber, and was very popular with police and civilian users in the self-defense and backup gun role, especially in the United States.

The Star PD improved on its predecessor (Star Model PKM) by using a low-profile adjustable rear sight and by removing material from the slide and other small changes. These modifications, combined with its aluminum alloy construction, resulted in a slim, compact, lightweight and relatively powerful pistol, revolutionary for the time. As it also bore an external resemblance to the well-known M1911 pistol, the gun sold very well in the U.S. until it was replaced in 1990 by the Firestar M45.

Details

Everything you need to turn your stripped lower into a rifle for one low introductory price.  Kit includes a PSA 16" Hammer-Forged, Chrome-Lined, M4A1 upper, BCG, charging handle and our Classic Lower Build Kit.

Lower Build Kit:  Includes our M4-style stock, A2 Pistol grip, Palmetto State Armory Classic Lower Parts Kit and Mil-Spec size buffer tube, castle nut, end plate, carbine spring, and PSA Standard buffer.

Barrel:  A proprietary blend of Hammer forged chrome molly vanadium made by FN that is referred to as "Machine Gun Steel" by virtue of its use in FN's M249 and M240 weapons.   The hammer forging process work hardens the steel, making it more durable.  In addition, the chrome process for the bore allows for a lining almost twice as thick as a standard M16 for enhanced durability. Upper: Forged 7075-T6 A3 AR upper is made to MIL-SPECS and hard coat anodized black for durability. Featuring machined T marks, and a mil-spec finish. These uppers are made for us right here in the USA by a mil-spec manufacturer, and are marked with the Palmetto State Armory logo on the left side, up front, just below the rail.

Bolt: Bolt is made of Mil-spec Carpenter 158 steel, Shot peened, MPI and HPT. Gas key is secured with grade 8 fasteners and staked per mil-spec. Bolt carrier is parkerized outside, chrome lined inside, and laser engraved with the Palmetto State Armory logo.

title: For Sale:  Gunsmith & Custom Firearms
postcontent:
Visit us online! http://www.ExtremeFirepower.com/

Gunsmithing

Let EFI, LLC's experienced gunsmith keep your firearms in top working order! Our specialties include Sig Sauer Pistols, AR15/M16 Series, UZI, 1911 Pistols, Remington Rifles, and HK 90-Series. Otherwise, we offer accurizing, customization, repair, and refinishing services for most types of Title I and Title II firearms.


Engraving

Whether you need a quick turn-around for engraving your receiver for a short-barreled rifle, or you would like a custom graphic on your gun, EFI, LLC can meet that need. Price will vary based on number of characters or complexity of graphic.


Parkerizing

EFI, LLC will take your firearm, disassemble it, inspect all parts for wear and advise you if any should be replaced to keep your firearm in good working order. We will then remove the current finish and any contaminants, and prepare the surface using a grit blast method that allows for a stronger finish to be applied. After the parkerization process is complete, we will again inspect, clean, lubricate, and reassemble your firearm. Both zinc and manganese parkerizing are available.


Consignments

If you would like to sell a gun then consign it with us! Our consignment fees are some of the lowest in the business - just check out our consignment agreement.


Custom Rifle Builds

EFI, LLC designed the bolt-action Precision Strike rifle system and the semi-auto Rapid Strike rifle system for professional shooters. We guarantee at least half minute of angle accuracy* from every one that we deliver. Options include custom barrel lengths and a variety of caliber choices. The rifles are available with an airline-approved hard case, scope, bipod, cleaning system, tools, and a sound suppressor (where local laws permit).

Firearm photographer Oleg Volk recently profiled one of our Precision Strike rifles in .338 LM on his blog. You can see what he has to say about it at http://olegvolk.livejournal.com/922647.html and http://olegvolk.livejournal.com/924824.html.

*Accuracy guarantee for a trained shooter using quality ammunition from a fixed position.


Transfers

Title I Firearms: $5

Title II Firearms: $25

No, those aren't typo's. We really do charge just $5 per Title I transfer. 

Do you have an FFL? Then check out http://www.FFLOnly.com/, a discussion forum run by and for FFL's (sorry, no C&R).

title: For Sale:  AR Upper
postcontent:
I am selling my brother's AR upper.  This was used on 2 different tours of Baghdad, and has about 1000 rounds through it.  He bought the upper from PK Firearms prior to the first deployment, and added in accessories afterwards.  From there, he just checked the M4 lower out of the armory, and used this upper for the duration of both tours.  I'll try to be as thorough as possible for the description, please email me with any questions.

It has the Daniel Defense rail assembly, and is very similar to the 10.225" uppers found on the PK Firearms website.  The charging handle is slightly over sized for easier racking of the bolt carrier group.  This barrel is free floating, and has a standard A2 flash suppressor, rather than the ones pictured on their webpage: http://www.pkfirearms.com/Daniel_Defense_Custom_Uppers/156/c

He mounted a Surefire flashlight in a 1" Weaver mount to the front.  This is a Surefire 660 Classic Model.  It has the pressure-mount input, and it has a tape switch for remote-control.

He is running an Aimpoint Comp M2 w/ 2MOA dot and 2x magnifier.  The optics are very clear, and the knobs all work flawlessly.  As you can see, the front cover is still there, however Baghdad stole the rear cover.  Both could probably use a replacement anyways, and I just found them for around $40 online:  http://www.militarywarfighter.com/ProductDetails.asp?ProductCode=Aimpoint-12223-12224&gdftrk=gdfV21636_a_7c75_a_7c4662_a_7cAimpoint_d_12223_d_12224.  

The mount for the Aimpoint is an Aimpoint QRP, same as this one here:  http://store.a51tactical.com/index.php?main_page=product_info&products_id=2085&cPath=250#googlebase

The standard military "Grip Pod" Bipod fore-grip is still mounted to the front, these are about as rugged and durable as it gets.  Brownell's has them for $150, but I think that is a little high, so let's call it a $75 value.  I believe this one is a GPS2, as it has steel reinforcements in the legs.  I have one on my personal AR-15 Upper, and I doubt you will find a better one out there:  http://www.grippod.com/

There is a sling adapter on the left side, probably some sort of military issue, no idea there...  

Also, there is a rear sight assembly.  One of the viewers on here sent me a message saying it was a military issue rear sight.

This gun is in great shape, all things considered.
